comments: Antetokounmpo (MIL) is already in Tatum's (BOS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver any additional contact.
Horford (BOS) is in Bledsoe's (MIL) path in a screening position and he does not deliver the contact.
LAR shows Irving (BOS) loses control of the ball on his own and not as a result of any contact from Bledsoe (MIL).
Bledsoe (MIL) legally contests Irving's (BOS) shot near the rim.
There is no clear and conclusive video evidence that shows if Morris (BOS) makes contact to Bledsoe's (MIL) arm when he contests the shot attempt.
LAR and RAR show Horford (BOS) firms up in Bledsoe's (MIL) path and he does not deliver contact when it occurs.
Bledsoe (MIL) legally contests Irving's (BOS) shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) legally boxes out Horford (BOS) underneath the rim during the rebound.
Tatum (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position in Middleton's (MIL) path and the contact is incidental.
[Observable in enhanced video] Antetokounmpo (MIL) moves his pivot foot after his gather.
Horford (BOS) makes contact to Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm during his shooting motion prior to making any contact with the ball.
[Detectable with stop watch] Antetokounmpo (MIL) takes longer than 10 seconds to release his free throw.
Lopez (MIL) is already in Horford's (BOS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver any contact with his arms.
RAR shows Morris (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly deflects the ball away from Antetokounmpo (MIL).
Horford (BOS) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt.  Any 'high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
[Observable in enhanced video] Prior to the held ball, Antetokounmpo (MIL) slides his pivot foot.
Smart (BOS) gets both hands on the ball while Antetokounmpo (MIL) has possession and a held ball is called.

[Observable in enhanced video] At the time of the jump ball, there are 0.2 seconds remaining on the shot clock.  Antetokounmpo (MIL) tips the ball to Lopez (MIL), who does not control the ball and attempts a tip-in with two hands.  By rule, the only type of field goal he can attempt is a tip-in since there are fewer than 0.3 seconds remaining on the shot clock and a 24-second violation should not have been called.
Irving (BOS) is not established in a screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and he moves laterally into him, affecting his ability to defend the play.
Smart (BOS) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Following the contact from the screen by Irving (BOS), Middleton (MIL) grabs Morris (BOS) and affects his FOM.
[Observable in enhanced video] Antetokounmpo (MIL) extends his leg and makes contact with Irving's (BOS) leg, affecting his SQBR on his drive to the basket.
Bledsoe (MIL) moves A to B into Irving (BOS) and affects his driving shot attempt.
